The paper discusses techniques for robust subspace learning and tracking, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves matrix decomposition and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the use of sparse models, which is relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
